<sect2 id="plug-in-metadata-viewer">
  <title>Metadata Viewer</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Metadata</primary>
    <secondary>Metadata Viewer</secondary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    This plug-in allows you to view all Exif, IPTC, and XMP metadata present
    in the current image. To change or add metadata, you can use the
    <link linkend="plug-in-metadata-editor">Metadata Editor</link>.
  </para>

  <figure>
    <title>
      <quote>Metadata Viewer</quote> dialog
    </title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="images/menus/image/metadata-viewer-dialog.png"
format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <para>
      You can access this command from the main menu through
      <menuchoice>
        <guimenu>Image</guimenu>
        <guisubmenu>Metadata</guisubmenu>
        <guimenuitem>View Metadata</guimenuitem>
      </menuchoice>.
    </para>
  </sect3>

  <sect3>
    <title><quote>Metadata Viewer</quote> Options</title>
    <para>
      Each of the three metadata types is shown in its own tab. Check the
      links below for an explanation of what they are.
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <guilabel>Exif</guilabel>: see <xref linkend = "glossary-exif"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <guilabel>XMP</guilabel>: see <xref linkend = "glossary-xmp"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            <guilabel>IPTC</guilabel>: see <xref linkend = "glossary-iptc"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
